programDoc='''A computer program is a collection of instructions that tell a computer to perform a specific task.'''
memoryDoc='''Edison's microchip has the ability to store some things, like programs. These programs are stored in the robot's memory. We can tell Edison which of these programs we want to run by driving over special barcodes.'''
hardwareDoc='''All computers have two main parts: hardware and software. Hardware is the physical parts of a computer (or robot).'''
softwareDoc='''Software is the set of programs and applications that make hardware, like a computer or a robot, run.'''
variableDoc='''A variable is a bit of memory that is used to store a value in a program. You can think of a variable like a container that you can use to store some bit of information in a way that will make sense to a computer.'''